<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Leaves for Libya for OAU Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni has left for Tripoli, Libya where he will join other
African heads of state for an extraordinary meeting of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU).
</P>
<P>
Museveni, who was accompanied by his wife Janet Museveni, was
seen off at the Entebbe International Airport Monday afternoon by
Vice President Specioza Kazibwe and other senior government
officials, a press release from the President's Office said.
</P>
<P>
It is said that the meeting in Tripoli will address the issue
of economic integration of the continent as well as the charter of
the continental organization.  
</P>
