<HEADLINE> S. Africa Urges for Regional Police Networking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 6 (Xinhua) -- South African High Commissioner
to Zimbabwe Azwindini Ndou Monday called for regional networking
of police forces to stop the increasing flow of fire arms.
</P>
<P>
He told a security workshop here that increasing flow of fire
arms into South Africa is being used to commit violent crimes in
the country.
</P>
<P>
He added that the high levels of illegal immigrants had also
resulted in increased violent crimes in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Ndou dismissed the theory that since independence crime in
South Africa had gone uncontrolled.
</P>
<P>
"It is only that during the apartheid era some crimes in Soweto
went unreported, but now the system is more transparent, resulting
in those crimes being exposed," he said.
</P>
<P>
The workshop was being attended by security representatives
from Nigeria, South Africa, Zimbabwe and Interpol.  
</P>
</TEXT>
