<HEADLINE> Sweden to Provide Angola with $20 Million Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Luanda, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Sweden will provide Angola with
a humanitarian aid worth some 20 million U.S. dollars, to help
the country out of the penury caused by long-term civil war,
Swedish ambassador to Angola said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Official news agency Angop quoted Ambassador Lena Sund as
saying that his country will support humanitarian programs in
Angola in the next three years, and it has prepared 20 million
u.s. dollars "available" for the humanitarian aid.
</P>
<P>
Sund said that the his government had a review on the strategy
of the cooperation with Angola in this May and decided the aid to
the southwest African country which has suffered more than 30
years of war.
</P>
<P>
The aid came after a United Nation's appeal for helping Angola
out of the dilemma, said the ambassador.
</P>
<P>
According to Sund, Angola's programs for health, rehabilitation
of infrastructures and professional education will benefit from
the Swedish assistance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
