<HEADLINE> Greek Equity Prices Soar to New Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Greek equity prices surged to
new records Monday with the general index on the Athens Stock
Exchange (ASE) ending 3.95 percent higher at 5,621.67 points, its
46th record this year.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE/ASE 20 index Monday also rose 2.79 percent to 3,019.97
points.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 424.3 billion drachmas (about 1.4 billion U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Advancers led decliners by 286 to 25 with one issue unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The construction and holding sectors led the rising stock
market with ending 7.93 percent and 7.85 percent higher
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts attributed the sharp rise in the stock market
to confidence by people in the Greek government's economic policy
and the performance of listed companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
