<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Peacekeepers Kill Three Serbs in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Russian peacekeepers in Kosovo
on Monday shot dead three ethnic Serbs who attacked Albanians in
the Yugoslav province, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Russian patrol heard shots coming from Korminjane village,
northeast of Gniljane, on Monday morning and rushed to the scene,
Tass said, quoting the press center of the Russian military
contingent in Pristina, the regional capital.
</P>
<P>
The three serbs had attacked a car with three Albanians. The
Russian peacekeepers, when they arrived, found that the Serbs had
already killed one Albanian and were beating the other two
wounded.
</P>
<P>
The Russians ordered the Serbs to stop beating the Albanians,
but they responded by firing, and in accordance with the KFOR rule
of engagement, the Russians opened fire, killing all the three
Serbs.
</P>
<P>
None of the Russian peacekeepers was hurt in the incident, Tass
said, adding that the international U.N. police and the KFOR
military police are conducting an investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
