<HEADLINE> Peru's President to Attend APEC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Peru's President Alberto Fujimori
will attend the Asian Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) summit
in Auckland September 12-13, official sources said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The aim of President Fujimori' attendency to the APEC summit is
to enforce Peru's presence in the group after the Latin American
country has been admitted to it for nearly 10 months, said the
sources.
</P>
<P>
Peru joined the APEC on November 14, 1998, during the meeting
in Kuala Lumpur.
</P>
<P>
Other Latin American leaders including Chilean President Eduado
Frei and Mexican President Ernesto Zedillo have also confirmed
their attending to the summit. 
</P>
