<HEADLINE> Giant Turtle Discovered Injured in English Channel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 6 (Xinhua) -- A 200-kilogram giant turtle,
discovered injured on Sunday in the English Channel by French
yatchmen, has been brought to France, reported Agence
France-Presse.
</P>
<P>
The two meter long turtle, which is of the Luth race and an
adult, was first sighted off the beach of Chausey islands and
police Monday brought it to Granville, where a veterinarian is
treating it.
</P>
<P>
But experts said that the turtle does not have any chance to
survive because of its injured flippers and infection from the
wounds.
</P>
<P>
The Luth race turtles live in Guiana in south America and move
in the Atlantic in summer migrant season.
</P>
<P>
This turtle could have been pushed by the sea currents to the
English Channel. 
</P>
