<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arab, Israeli Leaders Enquire After Mubarak's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Arab and Israeli leaders
enquired after the health of Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
after he was injured in an assassination attempt Monday.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak was slightly injured by a clothing vendor in Port Said
when he was on his way to inspect industrial projects in the
Mediterranean port city at the northern end of the Suez Canal.
</P>
<P>
The clothing vendor, whom the Egyptian Interior Ministry later
identified as Hussein Mahmoud Solaiman, approached Mubarak's car
and inflicted a wound in his arm with a sharp tool, Egypt's Middle
East News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
The president's body guards fired at Solaiman and killed him.
</P>
<P>
After being treated with disinfectant, Mubarak went on to a
meeting and delivered a speech.
</P>
<P>
Following the speech in Port Said, Mubarak left for the Red Sea
resort of Sharm el-Sheikh in southern Sinai, where he received
telephone calls from Omani Sultan Qaboos Bin Said, Jordanian King
Abdullah and Saudi Crown Prince Abdullah. The Arab leaders
enquired after his health after the attack, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak received a similar call from Israeli President Ezer
Weizman, it added.
</P>
<P>
The Interior Ministry told the news agency that Solaiman, 40,
was a graduate of an industrial institute and a resident of Port
Said. He was a clothing vendor with "no political affiliations"
and "had been known for his impulsive behaviors and recklessness,"
the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak has survived at least three attempts on his life. The
most serious attack on him came in June 1995 when Muslim militants
fired at his limousine after it was driving out of Addis Ababa
airport of Ethiopia to a summit of the Organization of African
Unity.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak's predecessor, President Anwar Sadat, was assassinated
in 1981 by Muslim extremists angered by his signing of a peace
treaty with Israel in 1979. Mubarak, who was Sadat's vice
president, became president after the assassination.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak plays an active role in mediating the peace talks
between Arab countries and Israel, and cracks down severely on the
Muslim extremists who attempt to topple the secular Egyptian
government and install a strict Islamic rule. 
</P>
</TEXT>
