<HEADLINE> EU Issues Statement on Middle East Peace Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) said
Monday that it is ready to facilitate talks and implementation of
the existing agreements between the Israeli government and
Palestian Authority.
</P>
<P>
The EU "congratulates Prime Minister (Ehud) Barak and President
(Yasser) Arafat for the conclusion of difficult negotiations
between the parties of the Wye River agreement".
</P>
<P>
The memorandum is an important step which reestablishes
confidence and gives new optimism for accelerated final status
talks, the EU said in its presidency statement on the Sharm El
Sheikh Memorandum reached on Sunday between Barak and Arafat.
</P>
<P>
"The EU hopes that the memorandum opens the way for a final,
just, lasting and comprehensive peace within a reasonable
timeframe. All tracks of the peace process should now be activated
by taking concrete steps," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Finnishi Foreign Minister Tarja Halonen also sent a letter on
Monday on behalf of the European Union to Arafat, the Palestinian
Authority President, in order to support the memorandum for Middle
East peace process, the EU statement added. 
