<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Announce National Health Policy Shortly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Prime minister Sheikh Hasina
today said a national health policy attuned to the hopes and
aspirations of people would be announced shortly.
</P>
<P>
"Our government has been pursuing consistently a policy of
health development, particularly for the under-served rural
masses," she said.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister was inaugurating the week-long 52nd session
of the Regional Committee for the World Health Organization's
South East Asia Region at a city hotel.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the "Essential Package of Services" her government
is rendering to the entire population, the prime minister said
that "we are committed to ensuring health for all by the year
2006".
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said Bangladesh has been facing formidable
health problems due to the vicious cycle of population explosion,
poverty, low literacy rate and malnutrition. In addition there is
high prevalence of communicable diseases and particularly
preventable diseases among the children under five.
</P>
<P>
She said that "health for all by the year 2000" has been
accepted by her government as a national goal. Under this program
major emphasis has been given on reproductive health, child
health, communicable disease control, family planning and limited
curative care at all levels, she added.
</P>
<P>
Terming the burden of diseases as a matter of greater magnitude
in the South East Asia region, the prime minister called for
according highest priority to alleviate the curse of diseases,
disabilities and premature deaths. This calls for urgent policy,
increased budget and pragmatic initiatives from the governments
and close collaboration from developing partners, she said.
</P>
</TEXT>
