<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Euro Zone Unemployment Rate Falls in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brussels, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Euro zone seasonally-adjusted
unemployment rate fell to 10.2 percent in July 1999 from 10.3
percent in June, the European statistics office, Eurostat, said on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The figure of euro zone is 10.9 percent in July last year. The
rate in the whole European Union (EU) also fell to 9.3 percent in
July from 9.4 percent in June. And EU's unemployment in July last
year was 10 percent, the Eurostat said.
</P>
<P>
In the 15-country EU, lowest unemployment rate were Luxemborg
with 2.8 percent and the Netherlands with 3.2 percent, followed by
Austria with 4.3 percent, Portugal with 4.5 percent, and Denmark
with 4.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, unemployment rate in the United States was 4.
3 percent, and it was 4.9 percent in Japan, the Eurostat said in
its report.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Spain registered 15.9 percent unemployment rate, the
highest in the EU region. However, Spain did register a big fall
over the year, down from 18.8 percent to 15.9 percent, the report
indicated.
</P>
<P>
The Eurostat also estimated 13.2 million men and women were
unemployed in the euro zone and 15.8 million in 15 European Union
countries in July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
