<HEADLINE> Three People Killed in Heavy Rain in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, September 6 (Xinhua) -- At least three people were
killed and dozens of families were displaced on Monday as heavy
rains pouring on Somali capital since Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Two women and a child in northern Mogadishu were killed. One of
the women was killed after her poorly and least maintained house
had collapsed Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
The rain has also displaced dozens of families around the
former public house area of Hodon district in South Mogadishu
where the rainwater coming from many directions usually meet.
More than a dozen other families from the refugee camp near the
main soccer stadium have likewise fled their huts after the rains
washed away their makeshift houses.
</P>
<P>
Almost all public transport has stopped at mid Sunday. Many of
the main tarmac roads have been cut off and hampering business
activities in the capital,
</P>
<P>
The main business center of Somalia, the Bakara market of
Mogadishu, has been closed Monday after the rainwater has cut off
all the roads entering the market. All commodities including milk
and vegetables arriving from the suburbs have been trapped in the
middle of the roads for mud and water.
</P>
<P>
The rain is continuing for more than 30 hours consecutively.
</P>
</TEXT>
