<HEADLINE> Russia Hails Accord Between Israel, Palestinians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Russia said Monday that it
welcomes the agreements between Israel and Palestine on the
implementation of the accords concerning a transitional period for
the Palestinian territories.
</P>
<P>
Moscow duly appreciates "the Palestinian and Israeli leaders'
constructive approach, as well as the efforts made by the American
co-sponsor, by Egypt and personally by President Hosni Mubarak,"
the Russian Foreign Ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Last Saturday, Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat and Israeli
Prime Minister Ehud Barak met in the Egyptian city of Sharm el
Sheikh to sign a memorandum on the implementation of the mutual
obligations on these accords.
</P>
<P>
This memorandum also envisions "the initiation of talks on a
final status of the Palestinian territories to be completed by
September 2000," the Russian statement said.
</P>
<P>
"On our part we energetically promoted rapprochement between
the sides and strengthened their determination to implement the
assumed commitments," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
It expressed the hope that "a consistent implementation of the
agreements reached in Sharm el Sheikh will ensure steady progress
on the Palestinian track and have a positive impact on the
peaceful settlement as a whole."
</P>
<P>
"Talks on the complicated problems of final settlement, the
results of which will largely determine the future of the region,
will be of special importance," the Interfax news agency quoted
the statement as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
