<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Paraguay's President Names New Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Paraguay's President Luis
Gonzalez Macchi named Monday Jose Felix Fernandez as the new
foreign minister.
</P>
<P>
Fernandez is member of the Authentic Radical Liberal Party, the
largest opposition political figure and the governing Colorado
Party's main ally, according to reports reaching here from
Asuncion.
</P>
<P>
Former Foreign Minister Miguel Abdon Gonzalez Saquier was
removed from office last Saturday for failure to obtain the
extradition of two former military leaders who were granted asylum
in Argentina and Uruguay,
</P>
<P>
Argentina last Thursday rejected a request by Paraguay to
extradite failed coup leader former army chief Lino Oviedo, who is
accused of instigating Vice President Luis Maria Argana's
assassination in March. Oviedo requested political asylum in
Argentina on March 28.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay last Wednesday also turned down Paraguay's extradition
request for former Defense Minister Jose Segovia, alleged to be a
close associate of Oviedo.
</P>
<P>
Paraguay's government accuses Oviedo and Segovia of being
involved in the shooting of Vice President Argana on March 23 in
Asuncion's center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
