<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Never to Allow Independence of Taiwan: Cheng Siwei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 6 (Xinhua) -- A Senior Chinese Official
said here categorically that China will never allow independence
of Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Chen Siwei, Vice Chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress of China, stressed that to safeguard
national reunification and unity is the highest goal of the
Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Chen made the remarks at a banquet Sunday after the conclusion
of the 1999 International Symposium on "21st Century China and the
Challenge of Sustainable Development" which was co-sponsored by
Western Returned Scholars Association and 33 overseas Chinese
professional organizations in the United States.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has made its position on Taiwan very
clear, that is no independence, no "Two Chinas" and no "One China,
One Taiwan", Chen Siwei said.
</P>
<P>
Chen reiterated that Taiwan is an inalienable part of the
Chinese territory and the Chinese people will never tolerate
separation of Taiwan from the motherland.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Chinese government's consistent policy on the
Taiwan question is peaceful reunification on the basis of "One
Country, Two Systems", but China will not renounce the use of
force against Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
"Our policy on Taiwan has not changed, but if Lee Teng-hui and
the Taiwan authority go far and far on the road of separation,
Taiwan will possibly become a powder keg," Chen said.
</P>
<P>
Situation in the Taiwan Straits has grown tense after Lee
Teng-hui made his "state-to-state" doctrine on July 9th this
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
