<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Twelve smugglers involved in
a series of major cases in the south China city of Zhanjiang were
sentenced by a local court today.
</P>
<P>
The Intermediate People's Court of Zhanjiang in Guangdong
Province ruled that Pang Shixing, a former Customs officer, and
Tang Jingxin, a former Coast Guard officer, will have to spend the
rest of their life in jail, after both were convicted of bribery
and deprived of their political rights forever.
</P>
