<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Stage Chinese Arts Festival in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will stage a
Chinese arts festival to showcase Chinese music from October 22 to
November 13, an official from the Provisional Urban Council (PUC)
announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The festival, jointly sponsored by the PUC and the Provisional
Regional Council, will feature an exciting mix of music
performances complemented by talks, demonstration lectures,
workshops, exhibitions and a three-day music parade.
</P>
<P>
"Since 1991, the PUC has been presenting biennially a theme
festival respectively on Chinese drama, music, dance and opera,
all of which were well received," said Pao Ping-wing, chairman of
the PUC's Culture Select Committee.
</P>
<P>
He said that at the turn of the century, the festival provides
a unique opportunity to rediscover the gems of traditional music,
review masterpieces of the century as well as explore contemporary
endeavors.
</P>
<P>
With a rendezvous of more than 10 foremost music groups from
the inland, Hong Kong and Taiwan, it will feature three attractive
series lined up with 12 programs, according to Pao.
</P>
<P>
They are "Nostalgic Melodies Series", "Contemporary
Masterpieces Series" and "Beyond Y2K Series".
</P>
<P>
Apart from performances, the festival offers a series of
educational and extension activities. An exhibition entitled "Ten
Categories of Traditional Chinese Music Instruments" will be held
between October 19 and November 1 at the Hong Kong City Hall
Exhibition Hall.
</P>
<P>
Other activities include a three-day Chinese music parade
performed by local amateurs and students, lectures and
demonstrations, workshops and traditional Chinese music specials
on regional tunes and Cantonese operatic songs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
