</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- The European Commission said Tuesday that it has
approved a state aid for producers affected by the dioxin crisis
since the end of May in Belgium.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU) executive branch said the plan was
decided between the Belgian government and the Belgian Bank
Association.
</P>
<P>
The loan is designed to prevent the failure of the country's
basically sound agricultural undertakings, which suffer from an
income reduction as a result of a volatile market caused by the
dioxin contamination in some animal feeds and measures taken to
deal with the crisis. (EU-Dioxin-Aid)  
</P>
</TEXT>
