<HEADLINE> Chinese Girl Selected World's Best Letter Writer (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chen received the award after being named the world's best
young letter writer by the UPU and the United Nations Education
and Science and Culture Organization for her moving letter to her
cousin.
</P>
<P>
"In my eyes, the mail is like a gust of wind, which brings
friendship and love to all people in the world," said Chen, with
short hair and a child-like face.
</P>
<P>
Chen wrote the letter to tell her cousin about her friendship
with a Korean girl, saying that she got to know a Korean girl
named Shunji when she joined an international summer camp, and
after camp they kept in touch by mail.
</P>
<P>
Shunji later was afflicted with leukemia and Chen kept
consoling and encouraging her through letters, and also mailed
Chinese medicine to Shunji. After a time, Chen got a letter from
Shunji saying that she was recovering.
</P>
<P>
"The green-colored postal service is a link that connects
everyone the world over and plays an incomparable role in our
daily life," said Chen in her award-winning letter.
</P>
</TEXT>
