<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina Tuesday called upon all people irrespective of their
party affiliation and opinion to be united to eradicate illiteracy
in the country to face the challenges of the coming 21st century.
</P>
<P>
In a message on the eve of the International Literacy Day and
the National Adult Education Week, the prime minister said that
her government believes in the policy of turning the huge
population of the country into human resources.
</P>
<P>
