The DRC peace process got under way last week after an RCD
leadership dispute caused a six-week delay in putting into action
the July 10 peace accord to end the conflict.
</P>
<P>
Opposing factions of the rebel group were at odds over who
should sign the agreement on the RCD's behalf.
</P>
<P>
Both factions endorsed the peace accord on August 31, adding
their signatures to those of another rebel group and the six
countries involved in the year-long DRC conflict. 
