<HEADLINE> Taiwanese Encouraged to Invest in Mainland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Despite Taiwan leader Lee Teng-
hui's separatist "two states" remark, China will continue to
encourage Taiwanese investment in the mainland and further promote
economic and trade exchanges across the Taiwan Straits, a senior
Chinese official said here today.
</P>
<P>
"We'll stick to what President Jiang Zemin said, that economic
exchanges across the Straits should not be affected by any
differences," said Wen Zaixing, spokesman for the 3rd China
Investment and Trade Fair, which is to open tomorrow in the city
of Xiamen in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Wen said that China will take practical measures to protect the
legal rights and interests of Taiwan investors in accordance with
related laws and regulations.
</P>
<P>
Wen pointed out that Lee's remark has caused tense relations
between the two sides of the Straits and jeopardized both Taiwan's
economy and cross-Straits economic and trade ties.
</P>
<P>
However, Wen said, cross-Straits economic and trade exchanges
will keep on progressing as long as the Chinese on both sides join
hands in this efforts.
</P>
<P>
The annual China Investment and Trade Fair is the only national
investment and trade fair sponsored by China's Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation. A large number of business people
from Taiwan will attend this year's fair.  
</P>
