<HEADLINE> Jordanian King Keen on Developing Jordanian-Kuwaiti </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian King Abdullah
Bin Hussein on Tuesday asserted his keenness on promoting
relations and cooperation in all fields between his country and
Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
In a cable of thanks to Kuwaiti Emir Jaber Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah
after his two-day visit here, Abdullah said he was delighted with
the Kuwaiti leader's keenness to end almost one decade of
estrangement between the two countries, saying the decade was "a
past exceptional experience in their relations."
</P>
<P>
He expressed belief that bilateral ties between Jordan and
Kuwait will remain as a model of honesty, trust and sincerety, as
well as fruitfull cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Abdullah assured that Jordan will support Kuwait
to achieve a positive result concerning the issue of Kuwait's
prisoners of war, allegedly detained in Iraqi jails.
</P>
<P>
According to the Kuwait News Agency, Abdullah also invited
the Kuwaiti Emir to visit Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah was the first Jordanian monarch to visit Kuwait in
more than nine years. Ties between Jordan and Kuwait worsened
after the 1990 Gulf crisis triggered by Iraq's invasion of Kuwait,
during which Jordan was blamed for siding with Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Jordan and Kuwait began the rapprochement process more than
two years ago, after Kuwait voiced its desire to improve ties
with all Arab nations except Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Amman reopened its embassy in Kuwait last March during an
official visit by Jordan's Foreign Minister Abdul Ilah
Al-Khatib.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian cabinet recently appointed its new ambassador
to Kuwait, as part of the preparation for Abdullah's visit.
</P>
<P>
However, Kuwait is still represented in Amman by a charge
de'affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
