<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's 1st BOT Project Transferred </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- China's first BOT (Build,
Operate and Transfer) project, a large thermal power plant, was
transferred Tuesday by its Hong Kong investor to the local owner
in Shenzhen, Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony was held at the Shajiao No.2 Power Plant attended by
senior officials including Wang Guangying, a vice chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the ceremony, Wang said the project shows that the
Chinese government allows overseas investors to earn legal profits,
and they are always welcome.
</P>
<P>
The power station went into use in 1987, and by the end of this
July it had generated 46.2 billion kwh of electricity.
</P>
<P>
The plant has been hailed by experts as a successful BOT
project, since its operation has not only benefited the local
economy, but also the Hong Kong company that financed, built, and
operated it before the transfer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
