<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquake Rocks Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 7 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake hit Athens
around 3 P.M. local time Tuesday, rocking office and apartment
buildings and sending frightened residents into the streets.
</P>
<P>
The quake, measuring 5.9 on the richter scale, had an epicenter
in the Mount Parnitha region, some 20 kilometers northeast of
Athens, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Milder aftershocks from the quake continued to rattle the city
center, and residents, some of them with tears in the faces,
gathered in the streets and parks following the quake, which was
also felt throughout central Greece.
</P>
<P>
No injuries have been reported, but there was an unconfirmed
report of the death of one person due to a heart attack. Some
parked cars were damaged and a building near the Athens first
cemetery in the suburb of Pangrati collapsed under the force of
the quake. 
</P>
</TEXT>
