<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Approves Aid For Belgium's Dioxin-affected Producers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brussels, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said
Tuesday that it has approved a state aid for producers affected by
the dioxin crisis since the end of May in Belgium.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU) executive branch said the plan was
decided between the Belgian government and the Belgian Bank
Association.
</P>
<P>
The loan is designed to prevent the failure of the country's
basically sound agricultural undertakings, which suffer from an
income reduction as a result of a volatile market caused by the
dioxin contamination in some animal feeds and measures taken to
deal with the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be provided fifty-fifty by the Belgian government
and Belgium's private banking sector, according to the Commission.
</P>
</TEXT>
