<HEADLINE> China's Exports of Electronic Goods Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- China exported 20.53 billion
U.S. dollars worth of electronic products in the first seven
months this year, an increase of 23.7 percent over the
corresponding period of last year.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed here today by an official from the Ministry
of Information Industry, who spoke at the opening of an
international electronics exhibition.
</P>
<P>
The official ascribed this to the current government policy to
develop the information sector and stimulate demand in the
domestic market.
</P>
<P>
From January to July, China turned out 21.89 million lines of
program-controlled telephone exchanges, 8.08 million cellular
phones, and 1.66 computers.
</P>
<P>
During this period, the electronics industry generated 348.3
billion yuan in total output value, up 24.5 percent year-on-year;
43.63 billion yuan in added value, up 18.4 percent; 198.2 billion
yuan in sales, up 22.6 percent; and 15.1 billion yuan in pretax
profits, up 34 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
