<HEADLINE> Philippines Provides Calamity Loans to Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Social Security
System (SSS) has released some 678 million pesos (16.9 million
U.s. dollars) in calamity loans to 86,480 members who were
affected by floods in August, officials said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The amount could go up to over 1.8 billion pesos (45 million
dollars) as there are still 242,600 applications being processed.
</P>
<P>
Edgar Solilapsi, senior SSS official charged with loans and
investments, said some 382,600 calamity loan applications were
received from in last month.
</P>
<P>
Metro Manila and two other provinces in the vicinity were
earlier declared calamity areas following the continuous and heavy
downpour of monsoon rains that resulted in heavy floodings.
Thousands of houses were submerged in waters in Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
In response to the crisis, Solilapsi said, the SSS calamity
loans were released. The filing of the loan applications ended on
September 3, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
