<HEADLINE> HK Medical Delegation Visits Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 7 (Xinhua) -- A delegation from the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) today began an eight-
day visit to southwest China's Sichuan Province to explore joint
development in the field of traditional Chinese herbal medicines.
</P>
<P>
The trip is being sponsored jointly by the Ministry of Science
and Technology, the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the
State Council, and the Hong Kong branch of Xinhua News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The delegation consists of 31 officials, scientists, medical
experts and business people.
</P>
<P>
Through the visit, the participants will gain a comprehensive
knowledge and understanding of the province's medicinal herbs,
traditional-medicine education, development of new medicines,
pharmaceuticals, and medicine high-tech zones.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan, one of country's largest medicine-material producing
areas, has the country's only traditional medicine high-tech
industrial center, said one expert with the delegation, and Hong
Kong is rich in research professionals and facilities. Cooperation
and exchange between the two sides will help establish a number of
international medicine industrial groups. 
</P>
