paid a secret visit to the Panjsher valley, the stronghold of the
opposition forces loyal to former defense minister Ahmad Shah
Masood.
</P>
<P>
"Unfortunately such self-interested circles allow for the
continuation of fighting here with their subversive moves. They
also help the outcast groups to live a bit longer thanks to their
financial offers," the broadcast monitored here said.
</P>
<P>
The radio urged the international community to "handle things
responsibly" and help the Islamic country maintain the present
order instead of undertaking "illegal trips."
</P>
