<HEADLINE> Cote D'lvoire to Host 23rd UPC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Cote D'lvoire will host the
23rd Universal Postal Congress in the year 2004, Moussibahou Mazou,
Deputy Director General of the International Bureau of the
Universal Postal Union, announced today.
</P>
<P>
Mazou said at today's news conference that the ongoing
Universal Postal Congress (UPC) has approved Cote D'lvoire's
application and the next Congress will help promote postal issues
in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Daniel Kablan Duncan, prime minister of Cote D'lvoire, said
that his country will make every effort to ensure the success of
the Congress.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the present 22nd Congress is well-organized and
Cote D'lvoire will learn from China's the successful experience
and use its own advances to insure the success of the 23rd
Congress.
</P>
<P>
He cited his country's advantages as support from other African
countries, a stable political and economic environment, well-
constructed infrastructure, and experience in hosting previous
international conferences.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that his government will not only raise funds
itself, but also encourage private firms to support the Congress.
</P>
<P>
At today's news conference, Mazou also noted that the UPU will
strengthen technical support to developing countries and promote
cooperation and exchange among these countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
