<HEADLINE> HK to Issue Stamps on 50th Birth Anniversary of PRC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's acting
Postmaster General Kingsley Li announced Tuesday that a set of
special stamps on the theme of the "50th Anniversary of the
Founding of the People's Republic of China" will be issued on
October 1, China's National Day.
</P>
<P>
The stamps are designed by Tony Ho and printed in lithography
by Southern Color Print, New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
There are four stamps in this set and a mini pane consisting of
four sets of these stamps in special arrangement is available.
</P>
<P>
As from this Friday (September 10), the stamps will be
displayed for advance public information.
</P>
<P>
Other associated philatelic products include a presentation
pack containing the four stamps, a set of four picture cards with
airmail postage prepaid and a collector's stamp pack.
</P>
<P>
The collector's stamp pack comprises the mini pane and a stamp
sheet which was entitled the "50th Anniversary of the Founding of
the People's Republic of China - Unity of Nationalities" and
issued by the State Post Bureau, PRC.
</P>
<P>
A special postmark will be introduced to commemorate the event.
</P>
