<HEADLINE> DuPont Adopts New Direction in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- DuPont China Co., Ltd. will
enhance its investment in the hi-tech fields in China as an effort
to cater to the U.S.-base multi-national company's new corporate
direction and new positioning as a science company.
</P>
<P>
To demonstrate its new policy, the company has substituted its
65 year old slogan of "Better Things for A Better Life" with "The
Miracles of Science."
</P>
<P>
"The new positioning is aimed at shifting the 200 year old
company's emphasis from a chemical to a science base," said
Kathleen Forte, Vice President of DuPont.
</P>
<P>
To reach that goal, the company has withdrawn from the energy
sector and adjusting the level of its chemical business while
increasing investment in life science.
</P>
<P>
"The last two years have witnessed DuPont's investment of over
14 billion U.S. dollars in life science sectors such as
pharmaceuticals, food ingredients and agricultural biotechnology,"
said Forte, adding that the investment is more than half of the
company's total sales today.
</P>
<P>
She noted that DuPont is now expanding its investment to areas
of biology, agronomy, genetics and catalysis.
</P>
<P>
Not long ago, DuPont also appointed a new vice president in
charge of its internet section, she said.
</P>
<P>
"In the meantime, DuPont China is expected to set up more
technology development branches and it is exploring cooperation
with China's Agriculture Ministry on the agricultural
biotechnology research," said Li Qing, general manager of DuPont
China.
</P>
<P>
Li also said that DuPont China will help to sponsor a seminar
during a science and technology festival taking place in Shanghai
this October.
</P>
<P>
The company is preparing the launch of the DuPont science award
together with the Ministry of Science and Technology of China, Li
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
