<HEADLINE> HK Foreign Currency Assets Reach 89.2B U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary
Authority (HKMA) announced Tuesday that the official foreign
currency assets of Hong Kong amounted to 89.2 billion U.S. dollars
at the end of August 1999.
</P>
<P>
Including unsettled forward contracts, the foreign currency
assets of Hong Kong at the end of August 1999 stood at 89.3
billion U.S. Dollars, according to a spokesman for the HKMA.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that in terms of foreign currency reserves
ranking, Hong Kong is the world's fifth largest holder of foreign
currency reserves after Japan, China's inland, Taiwan and Germany.
</P>
<P>
The total foreign currency assets of 89.2 billion U.S. dollars
represent over seven times the currency in circulation or about 37
percent of Hong Kong dollar M3, one of the highest ratios in the
world, the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
