<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean National Trade Union to Launch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 7 (Xinhua) - Leaders of the Zimbabwe Congress
of Trade Unions (ZCTU), the country's largest national labor
organization, said the union-sponsored political party, the
Movement for Democratic Change, will be launched in Harare on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference Monday in Harare, ZCTU President
Gibson Sibanda said the country was facing social and economic
crises that had made the formation of an alternative formidable
political movement imperative, the daily Herald reported on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He said the incumbent government had failed to offer solutions
to the problems afflicting Zimbabwe and alleged that there was
growing corruption among top government officials.
</P>
<P>
