living in the country and abroad to reclaim their power from those
who have misused it, to put in place a new leadership and
political system which will work in the interest of the people and
the nation," he said.
</P>
<P>
The new party will represent the interests of people from all
walks of life, he added.
</P>
<P>
On relations between the new party and the ZCTU, he said
although there would be distinctions on the operations of the two,
the party would continue to draw its power from the workers'
movement.
</P>
<P>
"The ZCTU will retain its autonomy but, remember, it is the
workers who decided that we go this path. The relationship
between the two will be that of a strategic alliance," he said.
