<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Exchange Index Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices of the Karachi
Stock Exchange (KSE) fell Tuesday amid heavy selling in blue chip
stocks owing to shaky confidence of investors after the general
strike held country wide last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The KSE-100 index closed 18.97 points, or 1.63 percent lower to
1147.43 against 1166.40 last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The total volume of the trade on Tuesday stood at 99.511
million shares against last Friday's 150.848 million shares.
</P>
<P>
"The high carry over transaction (COT) charges on Friday
coupled with the Saturday's strike in the country particularly in
Karachi depressed the mood of the investors as they fear that
unification of opposition would weaken the government and create
political uncertainty in the country," said Faisal Abbas, a dealer
with Ali Husain Rajabali Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Abbas said the investors were reluctant to take new positions
and in addition the local institutions were also keeping
themselves to the sidelines due to lack of interest which
encouraged the sellers to take control of the market.
</P>
<P>
Of the 156 active issues, losers beat gainers 72 to 34 while 50
remained unchanged. 
</P>
