<HEADLINE> UPU Celebrates 125th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Universal Postal Union (
UPU) held a grand ceremony in Beijing today to celebrate the 125th
anniversary of its founding.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from more than 170 member countries of the UPU
and over 30 international organizations attended the event held at
Beijing's International Post Office.
</P>
<P>
Liu Liqing, vice-president of the Chinese Organizing Committee
of the ongoing 22nd Universal Postal Congress (UPC) and postmaster-
general of the State Postal Bureau (SPB), said at the ceremony
that it is a great honor for China Post to host both the UPC and
the 125th anniversary celebrations of the UPU. He expressed the
wish to strengthen cooperation with postal services in other
countries.
</P>
<P>
Andre Darrigrand, the Doyen of this UPC, said that he would
like to see post offices in all countries bringing postal services
into the new millennium with a new creative effort.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Leavey, the re-elected director-general of the
International Bureau of the UPU, said that it has played an
important role in promoting inter-person exchanges in the world
over the last 125 years. He called on postal administrations in
all countries to find a point of balance between commercial and
human needs and strive to meet the needs of various customers.
</P>
<P>
At the ceremony, Leavey presented a gold medal to the winner of
the 1999 International Letter Writing Contest -- Chen Xinyi, a 12-
year-old girl from Wuxi city in Jiangsu Province in east China.
</P>
<P>
A bronze plaque marking the 125th anniversary of the UPU was
unveiled in front of the post office during the ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
