<HEADLINE> French City to Host Exhibition on Great German Poet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The city of Saverne in Bas-Rhin
of east France will host an exhibition on the great German poet
Wolfgang Goethe to mark his 250th birthday, the Agence France-
Presse reported.
</P>
<P>
With 450 objects, many of which are previously unpublished
documents, the exhibition is organized by the German government
and will move on to Bologne, Italy.
</P>
<P>
One of the rare curiosities to be presented in Saverne is a
letter written by Goethe to the daughter of the pastor of
Sessenheim, Frederik Brion.
</P>
<P>
The display also follows the trail of the tours made by Goethe
across Europe during his lifetime.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will be held from September 18 to October 31.
</P>
<P>
Goethe is regarded by France as one who has spread the French
culture to Germany, but he missed two chances of visiting Paris --
once by declining an offer of a diplomat's post there, another
time by turning down an invitation from Bonaparte Napoleon.
</P>
</TEXT>
