<HEADLINE> HKSAR Will Field Largest Team to Sydney: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region of China (HKSAR) is going to send its
largest sports contingent ever for the 2000 Sydney Olympic Games,
said a senior sports official here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We will be bringing a larger squad, probably over 50 athletes,
to the Sydney Olympics Games next year," said Pang Chung,
secretary general of the Sports Federation &AMP; Olympic Committee of
Hong Kong, China.
</P>
<P>
He confirmed that the contingent for Sydney must be larger than
the 49-competitor team for the last Olympic Games in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time for HKSAR to participate in Olympics
after Hong Kong returned to its motherland two years ago.
</P>
<P>
Pang said it was essential that they got more people to go to
the Olympics to promote sports in Hong Kong and encourage more
athletes to participate in next year's games.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong sent its first Olympic team to Helsinki in 1952, and
its wind surfer Lee Lai-shan won Hong Kong's first gold medal in
the Atlanta Olympic Games in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
