<HEADLINE> 2 Ethnic Party Activists Killed in Karachi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Two activists of the ethnic
Muttahida Qaumi Movement (MQM) were killed by police in a fierce
gun-battle in Karachi Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The MQM members were reported to be wanted in several cases of
murder.
</P>
<P>
Sources from Karachi said that the two MQM members opened fire
on police during a raid on a house in Orangi town in western
Karachi.
</P>
<P>
Police retaliated and the two MQM members were killed in the
gun- fire.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate response from MQM, a major opposition
party with its dominance in city areas in Pakistan's Sindh
province.
</P>
<P>
Three other MQM members were shot dead by police early this
month in two separate incidents in Karachi. 
