<HEADLINE> '99 International Flower Fair Opens in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- A month-long international
flower fair has opened in this capital city of northeast China's
Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The fair has attracted 280 exhibitors from many provinces in
China as well as 56 exhibitors from 15 countries and regions
across the world. The Netherlands, Japan, the Republic of Korea,
Israel, Turkey, Malaysia are among them.
</P>
<P>
Potted landscapes, ornamental plants, cactus, dried flowers,
root carvings and gardening wares as well as the newest scientific
research results on flowers are on display at the fair.
</P>
<P>
Seminars on flower planting and trade activities will also be
held during the 30-day event.
</P>
<P>
In organizing such a fair, Shenyang wants to make the floral
industry more commercialized and internationalized.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang is the industrial heartland in northeast China.
</P>
