<DOCNO> XIE19990907.0186 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CDB Vows Effective Use of Loans Supporting T-Bond Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The China Development Bank (
CDB) will give strong support to projects invested by the state's
newly issued 60 billion yuan treasury bonds and will ensure safe
and effective use of loans channeled to these projects.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the CDB said today that it will continue to
support infrastructure projects including highways, railways,
power supply networks and urban infrastructure construction, and
major support will also be given to technology and environmental
protection projects.
</P>
<P>
He said that the CDB will adhere to the principle of choosing
projects that are profitable, capable of repaying the principal
loan and interest and enjoy good market potential. No support will
be given to construction redundant projects.
</P>
<P>
By the end of August this year, the CDB had promised to invest
in 52 projects and had looked at 50 of them, with the promised
amount of loans totaling 50.48 billion yuan, of which 11.4 billion
yuan will be extended this year.
</P>
<P>
"To ensure safe and effective use of these loans, the CDB will
speed up project appraisal procedures and facilitate capital
allocation," the spokesman said, adding that the bank will
strengthen its supervision on the use of the loans and project
quality.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the CDB granted loans of 31.9 billion yuan to support
project investments following the state's issuance of 100 billion
yuan in supplementary T-bonds, accounting for 32 percent of such
loans by all commercial banks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
