<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets Kuwaiti Deputy PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu
Jintao met with visiting Kuwaiti Deputy Prime Minister and Defense
Minister Sheik Salem Sabah Al-Salem Al-Sabah and his party at the
Great Hall of the People today.
</P>
<P>
Hu said friendship between China and Kuwait can be traced back
to ancient times, and bilateral ties have witnessed considerable
growth since the establishment of diplomatic relations in 1971.
</P>
<P>
"The Kuwaiti government and people, under the leadership of
Emir Al-Jaber Al-Sabah, are devoted to safeguarding national
security and regional peace and stability," Hu said, adding that
China highly appreciates Kuwait's eye-catching achievements in
rebuilding the country on the back of war debris.
</P>
<P>
He thanked Kuwait for its support for China on issues
concerning Taiwan and human rights. The Chinese government and
people cherish the traditional friendship between the two
countries and are willing to push forward bilateral ties to a
higher level through joint efforts.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed the guests on China's stance on the current
regional and international situation and also the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
Al-Salem said there is traditional friendship between the two
armies and the two countries, and the purpose of his delegation's
current visit is to further deepen such a relationship. He also
reaffirmed the Kuwaiti government's pursuit of the "one China"
policy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
