<HEADLINE> World Largest Timepiece Trade Fair Opens In HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Watch and Clock
Fair '99, the largest of its kind in the world, opened here
Tuesday, attracting a total 780 exhibitors from 15 countries and
regions.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong watch and clock manufacturers continue to embrace
the latest technologies such as 3-dimensional computer-aided
design, rapid prototyping techniques and metal injection moulding
to further enhance their competitiveness," said Benedict Sin, co-
chairman of the fair's organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, one of the world's leading watch and clock exporters,
is the natural venue for the world's largest specialized timepiece
exhibition, Sin told the opening ceremony of the fair.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's sales of watches and clocks in 1998 totaled over 44.
2 billion HK dollars (5.66 billion U.S. dollars), according to Sin.
</P>
<P>
"The fair is an ideal opportunity for buyers from around the
world to source all types of watches, clocks and related products,
" Sin said.
</P>
<P>
Among the highlights at the fair will be the Asian Watch
Industry Conference to be held on September 9 at which experts
from Japan, the Middle East, Europe and the United States will
share insights into opportunities in their home markets.
</P>
<P>
The fair, which runs until September 11 at the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center, is co-organized by the Hong Kong
Trade Development Council, the Hong Kong Watch Manufacturers
Association Ltd., and the Federation of Hong Kong Watch Trade and
Industries Ltd. 
</P>
</TEXT>
