ALMA ATA -- The Kyrgyzstan Foreign Ministry said Monday that
the government will eliminate the militants entrenched in the
south of the country and rescue the hostages.
</P>
<P>
A month ago, 400 militants invaded the area of Osh in the south
of Kyrgyzstan near Tajikistan. The militants are currently "holed
up" in a mountainous village and are still holding 12 hostages,
including Shamkeyev, the commander of the interior ministry troops,
and four Japanese geologists. (Kyrgyzstan-Hostage)
