1982 Constitution at the opening ceremony of the new juridical
year held on Monday, saying that "the 1982 Constitution was
approved under threat."
</P>
<P>
He said that "the majority of 93 percent is a shameful
majority that is seized by an attack on the honor of people and we
can't welcome a new century with a constitution that bids
republican system instead of democracy and whose legality is
zeroed."
</P>
<P>
Sabah (Morning):
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit commented the
statements made by Supreme Court Head Sami Selcuk, saying that
"everybody must understand these statements very good and attach
them due importance. We need to adopt constitutional amendments
particularly for the aim of complete freedom of the judiciary."
