<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Launches "Love Your River Month" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Tuesday launched
the national level "Love Your River" Month as part of its efforts
to ensure ultimately all rivers in the country are clean and free
of pollution.
</P>
<P>
Beautification and cleaning-up works on 423 of the 1,800 rivers
in the country have been intensified by the Drainage and
Irrigation Development (DID), an official of the Agriculture
Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The campaign was launched by the Agriculture Ministry's
Secretary- General Annuar Ma'aruf in the northeastern state of
Terengganu, Bernama news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In efforts to keep the rivers clean, local authorities should
provide proper garbage disposal sites for people in riverine
settlements, the official said, adding however, the most important
aspect of keeping the rivers clean is public awareness and
responsibility.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the pollution level of the country's
rivers was under control and so far there was no river which was
beyond redemption.
</P>
<P>
Last year 20 rivers in Malaysia were categorized as "very
polluted" but some of them had been cleaned up, he said.
</P>
<P>
The DID spends 5 million ringgit (about 1.315 million U.S.
dollars) annually on river cleaning-up and beautification works
nationwide.
</P>
<P>
During the "Love Your River" campaign, activities to be carried
out include river adoption, river watch, education and lectures,
river expedition and river beautification. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
