<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The 3rd International Seminar
on Management of Chinese and British Enterprises in a Changing
Business Environment opened today in the northern China port city
of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 entrepreneurs and officials from China and the
United Kingdom attended the opening session in the Tianjin
Economic Development Zone.
</P>
<P>
Han Songlin, deputy director of China Posts and
Telecommunications Bureau, John Perryman, managing director of
British Steel (Asia) Ltd., and 12 other guests will speak on the
economic situations in the two countries at the gathering.
</P>
<P>
The participants will discuss reforms in the power industry and
post and telecommunications sector, market development, management
expertise on technological renovation and foreign investment,
among other topics.
</P>
<P>
The seminar, part of a five-year governmental training
cooperation program, is jointly sponsored by China's State
Economic and Trade Commission and the British Trade and Industry
Department, aiming at improving the professional quality of
Chinese managerial personnel. The first two seminars were held in
Beijing and Shanghai, respectively.
</P>
