<HEADLINE> Chinese, Guinean Military Leaders Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, the chief of
General Staff of the People's Liberation Army (PLA), in talks here
today with his Guinean counterpart Ibrahima Diallo, pointed to the
deep traditional friendship between the people and the military
services of their countries, which has developed more in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his gratitude to the Guinean government for its
adherence to the "one China" policy and its support on issues like
human rights, and said he believes that the friendship and
cooperative ties between the two countries and their armed
services will be further developed through joint efforts.
</P>
<P>
Fu also explained China's views on the international situation,
its defense policy and military development, and reiterated China'
s stance on the Taiwan issue, emphasizing that the PLA is
determined, confident, and able to safeguard the sovereignty and
territorial integrity of the country and maintain unity.
</P>
<P>
Diallo said that because China is an important force in
maintaining world peace and stability, Guinea hopes that it will
have an even greater role in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Guinea is grateful for China's long-term support and aid, he
said, expressing his hope that the two countries will further
expand cooperation and exchanges. He also reiterated the Guinean
government's firm commitment to the "one China" policy.
</P>
<P>
Diallo began his nine-day China visit today. He is here at Fu's
invitation.  
</P>
