<HEADLINE> Chinese President Arrives in Australian Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
arrived here Tuesday to continue his state visit to Australia.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's plane landed at 5:10 p.m. local time (0710 GMT) at the
Royal Australian Air Force Base, where Australian Governor-General
William Deane and his wife Helen Deane, and Australian Prime
Minister John Howard and his wife Janette Howard greeted Jiang and
his wife Wang Yeping.
</P>
<P>
At the air force base, red carpets were rolled out and Jiang
was honored with a 21-gun salute and a royal salute before
reviewing guards of honor.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, the first Chinese head of state to set foot in Australia,
is here on the second leg of his state visit to the country.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Canberra, President Jiang is expected to
hold separate talks with the governor-general, the prime minister,
President Margaret Reid of the Senate, Speaker Neil Andrew of the
House of Representatives, and members of the Australia-China
Parliamentary Group.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang will exchange views with Australian leaders on
bilateral relations, as well as international and regional issues
of common interest.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's five-day trip will also take him to Sydney and Cairns,
from where he will leave for New Zealand to attend the seventh
informal meeting of leaders of the Asia Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) forum.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang arrived in Melbourne on Monday after winding up
his state visit to Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's entourage, including Vice Premier Qian Qichen and his
wife Zhou Hanqiong, also arrived in Canberra. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
