<HEADLINE> At Least Seven Killed in U.S. House Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 6 (Xinhua) -- At least seven people were
killed and nine others injured as a house exploded in Richland of
Iowa State, the United States, Monday afternoon, reports reaching
here said.
</P>
<P>
The explosion destroyed the ranch-style home and cars parked
outside. Light smoke was still coming from the charred debris
hours after the blast.
</P>
<P>
The dead were found in the basement of the house, and the
injured were taken to local hospitals, three of them in critical
condition.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the explosion was still unknown. 
