<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's High-Tech Zones Producing Wealthy Ventures (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- China's high-tech development
zones have 68 ventures with annual incomes of more than a billion
yuan (1.2 million U.S. dollars) after 8 years of development.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Science and Technology Zhu Lilan says that her
ministry is pushing for the adoption of a high-tech development
zone law and is encouraging several of them to become major high-
tech parks.
</P>
<P>
China's 52 industrial high-tech development zones have 9
corporate groups with annual incomes above 5 billion yuan, 7 of
which are solely Chinese, like Legend, Haier, Changhong Hisense,
and Beida Founders.
</P>
<P>
According the state development plan, the annual incomes of 52
state-level high-tech development zones is expected to reach 500
billion yuan by the end of 2000, or about a fifth of the country's
increased industrial output value.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Chaoying, who is in charge of high-tech development zones,
says that the rapid development has depended on high-tech
developments of Chinese scientists and improvements of foreign
technology. By the end of 1998, 76 percent of their products were
developed by Chinese scientists and they had over 16,000 ventures
making 480 billion yuan in all.
</P>
<P>
Per capita output value of the high-tech development zones was
240,000 yuan, much higher than the average of the country's
industrial ventures. About 80 percent of the zones focus on
electronics, information, bio-tech products, new materials, new
energy, energy saving devices, and environmental protection.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
