<HEADLINE> Fishing Boat Sinks in Philippines With 10 Missing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Ten crew members of a fishing
boat are still missing since their boat sank off the southeast
Philippine island of Palawan Friday night, reports reaching here
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The boat with 25 crewmen aboard was sailing from Manila to the
small island of Sulu near Zamboanga city when it encountered giant
waves causing it to capsize and sink off Palawan, Philippine News
Agency (PNA) said.
</P>
<P>
PNA quoted Zamboanga official sources as saying that some 15
survivors were fished out by rescuers from the waters.
</P>
<P>
The majority of the fishing boat's crew members are natives of
Zamboanga city, PNA said.
</P>
<P>
The 15 survivors are doing fine except for one who remains
unconscious due to apparent dehydration in a 40-hour sea ordeal,
the report added. 
