<HEADLINE> Avalanche Blocks Route Linking Argentina, Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 6 (Xinhua)-- A snow and stone avalanche
of 60 meters long erupted in the surroundings of international
tunnel Redeeming Christ, in Argentina's Mendoza province, on
Monday, thereby further blocking the way toward Chile.
</P>
<P>
Labor to clear the Route Seven toward the tunnel communicating
with Chile will take at least 48 hours if weather conditions allow,
the authorities said.
</P>
<P>
Redeeming Christ tunnel was cut off since Saturday evening
owing to a snowslide of 300 meters wide and six to seven meters
high which fell upon the Route Seven.
</P>
<P>
On the Chilean side three avalanches occurred recently.
