<HEADLINE> Chile, Central America to Sign Free Trade Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Chile and Central American
nations will sign a free trade treaty on October 25 in Santiago as
expected at the second summit of the states of the Americas (SOA)
held last year.
</P>
<P>
Presidents of Costa Rica, El Salvador, Honduras, Guatemala and
Nicaragua will visit Chile from October 24 to 26 for the event.
</P>
<P>
The treaty has been worked out after five rounds of
negotiations among the six countries since the SOA summit.
</P>
<P>
Vice ministers of foreign trade of the six countries met in
Costa Rica last week to define final details of the treaty.
</P>
<P>
Chile has signed similar accords with Canada, Mexico, Colombia,
Venezuela, Ecuador, Peru and Mercosur (South American Common
Market).
</P>
<P>
Chile is an associate member of Mercosur, which is composed of
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay. 
