<HEADLINE> Myanmar Innwa Bank Opens One More Branch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Innwa Bank Ltd., a
financial institution of the semi-official Myanmar Economic
Corporation, has opened one more branch in Myitgyina, northern
Kachin state of the country.
</P>
<P>
The fifth branch of the bank was inaugurated Monday, official
newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Innwa Bank earlier opened one branch each in Yangon,
Taunggyi, Mongshu and Mandalay townships, and is planning to set
up more branches in other townships.
</P>
<P>
Apart from providing local services, the bank also plans to act
as a corresponding bank of international banks with strong
financial power.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, there are 19 private banks
and three state-owned banks in Myanmar, providing domestic
commercial banking services.
</P>
<P>
The private banks in Myanmar hold about 45 percent of savings
deposits of the banking sector, while their loans account for
about 48 percent of the sector's loans to the private sector.
</P>
<P>
Altogether, there are about 70 private bank branches throughout
the country.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar embarked on market-oriented economic policy in late
1988 and reformed its banking system in 1990, allowing private
banks to operate again after they were nationalized in 1963.
</P>
</TEXT>
