<HEADLINE> Blair Meets Chinese Communist Party Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 6 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony
Blair said Monday that he hoped to see and would work for the
constant development of UK-China relations.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks when meeting with Ding Guangen, member of
the Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party's Central
Committee, at Downing 10 Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
In their friendly conversation, Blair extended welcome to Ding
on his visit, saying China is very important to Britain, and so is
Britain to China.
</P>
<P>
Ding, who arrived here on Sunday, said China attaches
importance to China-UK relations and hopes to see long-term, sound
and stable expansion of such relations, which he noted should be
treasured and safeguarded with efforts on both sides.
</P>
<P>
Ding said during his visit, he would made extensive contact
with the media in Britain. "The media play a special role in the
promotion of bilateral ties, for news coverage could contribute to
better understanding between the two peoples, and thus exert a
positive influence upon relations between the two countries," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Voicing agreement, Blair said he hoped to see strengthened
exchanges between the media of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Also on Monday, Ding met Chris Smith, British secretary of
culture, media and sports. 
</P>
