<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico to Donate Petroleum to DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican government
announced Monday it will donate the equivalent of 100,000 U.S.
dollars in petroleum for a program of industrial reconverting in
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK).
</P>
<P>
Mexico's energy support was requested by Japan inside the
Accord Framework for Peace, by which the DPRK renounced a nuclear
program, said the Secretariat of Energy.
</P>
<P>
The state company Mexican Petroleums (PEMEX) will deliver
officially the donation of crude to the embassy of the DPRK, said
the Secretariat of Energy.
</P>
<P>
Japan, main oil client of Mexico in Asia, heads the DPRK's
Industrial Reconverting Program inside the Accord Framework for
Peace with which the DPRK renounced a nuclear project.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican Foreign Secretariat will watch the fulfillment of
the donation of crude to the DPRK. 
</P>
</TEXT>
