<DOCNO> XIE19990907.0299 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Security Council Mission Makes Presentation to Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Security
Council appreciates the Indonesian government for its cooperation
with the U.N. in finding an internationally acceptable solution to
the East Timor question, the council said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The council is nevertheless seriously concerned about the
deteriorating security situation in East Timor, particularly since
the ballot on its future, it said in a presentation to the
government of Indonesia before its mission goes to Jakarta to seek
ways of halting violence in East Timor.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming the undertakings given by Indonesia to fulfill its
obligations under the May 5 agreement between Indonesia and
Portugal, the council said Indonesia's efforts so far "have not
been able to prevent an intensification of violence in the
territory."
</P>
<P>
The council decided to send an ambassadorial level mission to
Jakarta, urging Indonesia to ensure security and allow the U.N.
mission in East Timor, known as the UNAMET, "to implement its
mandate without hindrance."
</P>
<P>
The council mission, which met Secretary-General Kofi Annan
before its departure for Jakarta Monday night, is composed of
representatives of Namibia, Malaysia, the Netherlands, Slovenia
and Britain to the United Nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
